# Git — auto commit and fresh PR

When implementation is complete and required checks pass, **do not ask** whether to commit or open a PR. Finish the deliverable automatically.

## Commit (mandatory)

- Create a **fresh branch** per request or bugfix (never pile unrelated work onto an open PR).
- **Commit** all relevant changes without prompting the user.
- Do **not** wait for "please commit" unless the user explicitly asked to hold commits or the session is read-only/exploratory.
- Follow Git Safety Protocol: never update git config, no force-push to main/master, no `--no-verify` unless requested, no amend unless amend rules allow it.
- Use a HEREDOC for the commit message; summarize **why**, not just what.

## Pull request (mandatory)

- **Push** the branch (`git push -u origin HEAD`).
- **Open a new PR** with `gh pr create` (never reuse a merged/closed PR for new scope).
- Return the PR URL in the final response.
- Include Summary and Test plan in the PR body; list exact commands run and outcomes.

## Exceptions (only these)

- User explicitly says: do not commit, do not push, or hold for review.
- No file changes to commit.
- `gh` or remote auth is unavailable — report the blocker and leave exact commands for the user.

## Overrides

This rule **supersedes** any older user rule that says "only commit when requested" or "ask before opening a PR".
